| $f(\mathbf{C}_k, \mathbf{R}_k)$ | $= \dfrac{\mu}{2} \displaystyle\sum_{i,j} \left( \mathbf{C}_{k,ij}^2 + \mathbf{R}_{k,ij}^2 \right) + \dfrac{1}{2} \displaystyle\sum_{\mathbf{C}_{k,i:} \mathbf{R}_{k,:j} < \underline{\mathbf{M}}_{k,ij}} \left( \mathbf{C}_{i:} \mathbf{R}_{:j} - \underline{\mathbf{M}}_{k,ij} \right)^2 + \dfrac{1}{2} \displaystyle\sum_{\mathbf{C}_{k,i:} \mathbf{R}_{k,:j} > \overline{\mathbf{M}}_{k,ij}} \left( \mathbf{C}_{k,i:} \mathbf{R}_{k,:j} - \overline{\mathbf{M}}_{k,ij} \right)^2$ | (24) |
|---|---|---|
| $\dfrac{\partial f}{\partial \mathbf{C}_{k,ir}}$ | $= \mu \mathbf{C}_{k,ir} + \displaystyle\sum_{j : \mathbf{C}_{k,i:} \mathbf{R}_{k,:j} < \underline{\mathbf{M}}_{k,ij}} \left( \mathbf{C}_{k,i:} \mathbf{R}_{k,:j} - \underline{\mathbf{M}}_{k,ij} \right) \mathbf{R}_{k,rj} + \displaystyle\sum_{j : \mathbf{C}_{k,i:} \mathbf{R}_{k,:j} > \overline{\mathbf{M}}_{k,ij}} \left( \mathbf{C}_{k,i:} \mathbf{R}_{k,:j} - \overline{\mathbf{M}}_{k,ij} \right) \mathbf{R}_{k,rj}$ | (25) |
| $W_{ir}$ | $\triangleq \mu + \displaystyle\sum_{j : \mathbf{C}_{k,i:} \mathbf{R}_{k,:j} < \underline{\mathbf{M}}_{k,ij}} \mathbf{R}_{k,rj}^2 + \displaystyle\sum_{j : \mathbf{C}_{k,i:} \mathbf{R}_{k,:j} > \overline{\mathbf{M}}_{k,ij}} \mathbf{R}_{k,rj}^2$ | (26) |
| $\delta$ | $= -\dfrac{\partial f}{\partial \mathbf{C}_{k,ir}} / W_{k,ir}$ | (27) |
| $\mathbf{C}_{k,ir}$ | $\leftarrow \mathbf{C}_{k,ir} + \delta$ | (28) |
| $\mathbf{A}_{k,ij}$ | $\leftarrow \mathbf{A}_{k,ij} + \delta \mathbf{R}_{k,rj} \quad \forall j$ | (29) |
